# Exception Handling

## Global Strategy
- Use `@RestControllerAdvice` to handle exceptions globally.
- Return a consistent error response structure (e.g., `ErrorResponse`).

## Standard Exceptions
- `ResourceNotFoundException`: When an entity is not found (404).
- `BadRequestException`: When input is invalid (400).
- `BusinessException`: Base class for domain-specific logic errors.

## Handling Validation Errors
- Catch `MethodArgumentNotValidException`.
- Extract field errors and return a structured list of violations.

## Example
```java
@RestControllerAdvice
public class GlobalExceptionHandler {
    @ExceptionHandler(ResourceNotFoundException.class)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND)
    public ErrorResponse handleNotFound(ResourceNotFoundException e) {
        return new ErrorResponse("NOT_FOUND", e.getMessage());
    }
}
```
